### ðŸ“š Official Scikit-learn Documentation

1. **`fetch_20newsgroups` Dataset**
   - This is the dataset loader you used. It provides access to the 20 Newsgroups text dataset, widely used for text classification tasks.  
   - Documentation: Scikit-learn  [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fgenerated%2Fsklearn.datasets.fetch_20newsgroups.html")  
   - Key parameters:
     - `subset`: `"train"`, `"test"`, or `"all"`.
     - `categories`: list of categories to load (you used `['rec.sport.hockey', 'sci.space']`).
     - `remove`: allows stripping headers, footers, and quotes.

2. **Text Feature Extraction**
   - `TfidfVectorizer`: Converts text into numerical features using Term Frequencyâ€“Inverse Document Frequency.  
   - Documentation: Scikit-learn TfidfVectorizer [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fgenerated%2Fsklearn.feature_extraction.text.TfidfVectorizer.html")  
   - Important options:
     - `stop_words="english"` removes common English words.
     - `max_features` limits vocabulary size.

3. **Model Training**
   - `LogisticRegression`: A linear classifier well-suited for text classification.  
   - Documentation: Scikit-learn LogisticRegression [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fgenerated%2Fsklearn.linear_model.LogisticRegression.html")  
   - Key parameter: `max_iter=1000` ensures convergence on large datasets.

4. **Evaluation Metrics**
   - `classification_report`: Provides precision, recall, F1-score, and support for each class.  
   - `confusion_matrix`: Shows counts of correct and incorrect predictions.  
   - Documentation: Scikit-learn Classification Metrics [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fclasses.html%23module-sklearn.metrics")

